WEBVTT

00:01.750 --> 00:03.830
♪♪

00:03.830 --> 00:05.040
Dinner's ready!

00:07.000 --> 00:08.580
Last one in
washes the dishes!

00:12.750 --> 00:14.540
Looks like it's Mark!

00:14.540 --> 00:17.420
Okay, okay, before we eat,
tomorrow's Sunday,

00:17.420 --> 00:19.880
and I want everybody
dressed appropriately

00:19.880 --> 00:21.830
so we can pay our respects

00:21.830 --> 00:24.960
to the one thing that helps us
make sense of this world

00:24.960 --> 00:28.040
and gives us the strength
to make it through another week.

00:28.040 --> 00:29.540
Amen.
Amen.

00:29.540 --> 00:30.880
We're going to church?

00:30.880 --> 00:32.330
Come on! Harris!
On a Sunday?

00:32.330 --> 00:34.420
We're watching
the Bears-Packers game!

00:35.620 --> 00:37.460
But it is like church,
because when the Bears

00:37.460 --> 00:39.250
are collapsing
at the end of the game,

00:39.250 --> 00:42.540
we ask the Almighty
for a swift and merciful end.

00:42.540 --> 00:45.290
And win or lose,
we stick with the Bears.

00:45.290 --> 00:46.420
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Total commitment.

00:46.420 --> 00:48.580
Because if you're not
a true...fan --

00:48.580 --> 00:51.790
Oh, man! My Patriots receiver
is out for tomorrow.

00:51.790 --> 00:52.960
That could cost me.

00:54.460 --> 00:55.540
Are you gambling?

00:55.540 --> 00:57.000
Yep.
Fantasy football.

00:57.000 --> 00:58.790
Taking money
from a bunch of suckers.

01:00.250 --> 01:02.080
Oh, so it's like
a megachurch.

01:04.960 --> 01:07.290
No fantasy football tomorrow,
Jackie.

01:07.290 --> 01:09.120
We're only rooting
for the Bears.

01:09.120 --> 01:10.170
No distractions.

01:10.170 --> 01:11.420
Hey, can we eat already?

01:11.420 --> 01:13.080
I only came over here
to steal food and do laundry.

01:13.080 --> 01:14.710
I don't need
all this jibber-jabber.

01:14.710 --> 01:16.330
Eh, eh, eh, eh!

01:16.330 --> 01:19.000
That's not dinner.
That's for the game tomorrow.

01:19.000 --> 01:20.920
The SpaghettiOs on the stove --
that's dinner.

01:22.330 --> 01:23.420
Ugh.

01:23.420 --> 01:25.210
These aren't even
real SpaghettiOs.

01:25.210 --> 01:27.000
They're...Pisghetti Joe's.

01:28.540 --> 01:30.880
Come on, Mark, help me
get this food out to the garage.

01:32.330 --> 01:34.380
[ Groans ]
I hate football.

01:34.380 --> 01:35.750
Do I really
have to come tomorrow?

01:35.750 --> 01:37.620
It's important.

01:37.620 --> 01:39.580
I'm even bringing
this guy I've been seeing.

01:39.580 --> 01:41.420
Ohhhh!

01:41.420 --> 01:43.170
So, you checked the traps
lately, and you caught one.

01:44.420 --> 01:46.250
Hey, hey. Not cool.

01:46.250 --> 01:48.710
Does his wife know
he's coming over?

01:48.710 --> 01:51.000
This is why
you haven't met Wyatt yet.

01:51.000 --> 01:53.500
Wyatt!
Ohhh!
Wyatt! Well!

01:53.500 --> 01:55.210
Wait, wait.
What about Emilio?

01:55.210 --> 01:56.460
We've been
talking about it.

01:56.460 --> 01:59.000
He doesn't think
he can get back in the country,

01:59.000 --> 02:01.210
so we both decided
we should start dating.

02:01.210 --> 02:02.580
So, where'd you meet
this guy?

02:02.580 --> 02:05.500
We went out once
back when I was drinking.

02:05.500 --> 02:08.000
I threw up in the clown's mouth
at Putt-Putt.

02:09.880 --> 02:11.920
But Wyatt was so sweet.

02:11.920 --> 02:15.500
I got a text the next morning
that said, "Had a fun time.

02:15.500 --> 02:17.960
You're a blackout drunk.
Get help."

02:17.960 --> 02:19.710
Aww.

02:19.710 --> 02:23.290
I bumped into him about
a month ago with Beverly Rose.

02:23.290 --> 02:26.120
He saw that I'm sober
and even hotter now,

02:26.120 --> 02:27.580
and we've been dating
ever since.

02:27.580 --> 02:29.250
Ohh! Good for you.

02:29.250 --> 02:30.920
[ Jackie chuckles ]

02:30.920 --> 02:32.460
Okay,
what's wrong with him?

02:32.460 --> 02:33.830
Nothing.

02:33.830 --> 02:36.920
He treat me great,
he loves Beverly Rose,

02:36.920 --> 02:39.920
his mom and I DM on Instagram
all the time,

02:39.920 --> 02:42.920
and when the check comes,
he doesn't run.

02:44.120 --> 02:46.460
Darlene...he tips.

02:47.540 --> 02:48.880
He tips?

02:48.880 --> 02:51.330
He must be a millionaire.

02:51.330 --> 02:54.830
No. He's manager of Miracle Ear
at the mall.

02:54.830 --> 02:56.790
So he's
a really good listener.

02:56.790 --> 02:58.620
Uh, hold it.

02:58.620 --> 03:00.000
I know the problem.

03:00.000 --> 03:01.500
The sex is terrible,
right?

03:01.500 --> 03:02.750
We haven't done it.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.540
He knows I'm not ready yet

03:04.540 --> 03:07.080
because sober sex
is gonna be a whole thing.

03:08.290 --> 03:10.880
You gotta look at each other
in the eye.

03:12.330 --> 03:15.500
You gotta worry
about their feelings.

03:15.500 --> 03:18.500
I don't have the bandwidth
for that. It's terrifying.

03:18.500 --> 03:20.790
Don't worry.
The sex will happen.

03:20.790 --> 03:22.920
It wasn't the alcohol that made
you loose and indiscriminate.

03:22.920 --> 03:24.040
That's all you.

03:25.420 --> 03:31.420
Thanks.
That's what I thought, too.

03:32.330 --> 03:38.330
♪♪

03:40.460 --> 03:46.460
♪♪

03:48.580 --> 03:54.620
♪♪

03:56.710 --> 04:02.710
♪♪

04:06.750 --> 04:10.580
"The Conners" is
recorded in front of
a live studio audience.

04:10.580 --> 04:12.420
Good morning, sunshine.

04:12.420 --> 04:14.460
[ Groans ]

04:14.460 --> 04:15.670
Come on.

04:15.670 --> 04:16.880
It's time to get up.

04:16.880 --> 04:19.000
Oh, 20 more minutes.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.670
You moved back to Lanford
so we could start this paper.

04:21.670 --> 04:23.290
You've been in bed
for a week.

04:23.290 --> 04:25.000
[ Grunts ]
It's nice in here.

04:25.000 --> 04:26.420
Come snuggle.

04:26.420 --> 04:27.420
Ew!

04:27.420 --> 04:28.710
You need a shower.

04:28.710 --> 04:30.330
I don't wanna!

04:30.330 --> 04:31.420
Why not?

04:31.420 --> 04:34.670
Because I am planning
on taking a shower,

04:34.670 --> 04:37.080
but once I'm done,
I have nothing else planned.

04:38.670 --> 04:42.000
I'm not ready to face
an uncertain post-shower life.

04:42.000 --> 04:44.460
No.
It's not uncertain.

04:44.460 --> 04:46.830
Guess what -- I got a loan
broker to meet us this afternoon

04:46.830 --> 04:48.460
to get funding
for our new magazine.

04:48.460 --> 04:49.670
No.

04:49.670 --> 04:52.960
Today doesn't work for me.
It's my shower day.

04:52.960 --> 04:56.420
Look, I know you've been
in a funk since we got fired,

04:56.420 --> 04:58.540
but we don't have any money
coming in.

04:58.540 --> 05:00.170
I'm broke.

05:00.170 --> 05:01.960
You've seen my underwear.
It's not lace.

05:01.960 --> 05:04.420
It's just got
that many holes in it.

05:06.120 --> 05:07.460
[ Sighs ]

05:07.460 --> 05:09.620
I just don't think
I can get out of bed.

05:09.620 --> 05:10.790
I can help.

05:13.210 --> 05:15.580
Get out of bed!
Aah!

05:15.580 --> 05:16.960
Hey, hey!

05:16.960 --> 05:19.540
Now that leg's too long.
Do the other one.

05:21.290 --> 05:23.170
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

05:23.170 --> 05:26.210
If we have to watch this game,
can't we at least get a new TV?

05:26.210 --> 05:28.460
There are
so many dead pixels.

05:28.460 --> 05:31.420
It's like we're watching
through a chainlink fence.

05:31.420 --> 05:34.620
Yes, run, you bastard!

05:34.620 --> 05:38.040
Jackie, I told you.
No fantasy football.

05:38.040 --> 05:39.500
Lose the earbuds.

05:39.500 --> 05:40.540
Okay!

05:43.290 --> 05:44.880
She's got wired ones
in her back pocket.

05:44.880 --> 05:46.960
Oh, for God's sake!

05:49.750 --> 05:51.880
How?!
How can you drop that?!

05:51.880 --> 05:54.210
Come on! They pay you
to catch the football!

05:54.210 --> 05:55.710
Are you seeing this,
Mark?

05:55.710 --> 05:57.080
I'm sorry, what?

05:57.080 --> 05:59.830
I was looking
at a bird outside.

06:01.170 --> 06:02.380
A bird?

06:02.380 --> 06:04.880
This is
the Bears-Packers game!

06:04.880 --> 06:07.040
You gotta focus.

06:07.040 --> 06:09.500
Okay, I have something
to tell you, Grandpa,

06:09.500 --> 06:12.120
and I hope
you'll still love me afterward.
Yeah.

06:12.120 --> 06:13.880
I don't care
about football.

06:13.880 --> 06:15.920
[ Gasps ]

06:18.290 --> 06:19.790
Give me a minute, pal.

06:21.920 --> 06:25.880
I do still love you,
but everything's different now.

06:25.880 --> 06:28.330
I understand this gay thing,
but this is a choice.

06:30.290 --> 06:32.290
I've been pretending
to like it,

06:32.290 --> 06:34.580
but I just don't get
why this is so important.

06:34.580 --> 06:36.710
Because
when you're a Conner,

06:36.710 --> 06:39.080
you're not just part
of this family,

06:39.080 --> 06:41.790
you're part
of the Bears family.

06:41.790 --> 06:43.620
It's --
It's about tradition.

06:43.620 --> 06:46.250
I learned the game
from my grandpa,

06:46.250 --> 06:50.170
and the first time he took me
to watch Gale Sayers play...

06:50.170 --> 06:51.460
one of the best days
of my life.

06:52.920 --> 06:54.170
And he bought me a hat.

06:54.170 --> 06:56.170
And now
I'm giving it to you.

06:57.960 --> 06:59.120
I would've liked that hat.

07:00.750 --> 07:02.960
Thanks, Grandpa.

07:02.960 --> 07:04.880
Look at you!

07:04.880 --> 07:06.580
Now say, "Let's go, D!"

07:06.580 --> 07:08.290
Let's go, D!

07:08.290 --> 07:10.620
Now look
extremely disappointed.

07:10.620 --> 07:12.040
[ Sighs ]

07:14.960 --> 07:16.120
Now you're a Bears fan.

07:18.210 --> 07:20.170
Next thing
you need to know --

07:20.170 --> 07:21.460
we hate the Packers.

07:21.460 --> 07:23.290
Why?

07:23.290 --> 07:26.210
Because the Midwest
ain't big enough for both of us.

07:26.210 --> 07:28.000
But it's pretty big,
Grandpa --

07:28.000 --> 07:29.830
Just hate, would ya?

07:29.830 --> 07:31.960
[ Knock on door ]

07:31.960 --> 07:33.420
That's probably Wyatt.

07:33.420 --> 07:35.620
Everybody,
please go easy on him.

07:35.620 --> 07:37.500
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

07:43.170 --> 07:45.290
You didn't tell me
you were a Packers fan!

07:45.290 --> 07:47.330
Well,
I'm not rabid about it.

07:47.330 --> 07:49.040
I just thought
the cheesehead would be funny,

07:49.040 --> 07:50.830
like I'm one of those nuts
who puts on all the gear.

07:52.790 --> 07:53.750
It is funny.

07:53.750 --> 07:56.000
Let's put it in the car.

07:56.000 --> 07:58.170
Aw, come on. I'm not gonna
offend anybody with this.

07:58.170 --> 08:00.420
I wear it all the time
when I hang out with Bears fans.

08:00.420 --> 08:02.880
Those aren't Bears fans.

08:05.540 --> 08:08.040
These are Bears fans.

08:17.000 --> 08:18.620
[ Chuckles nervously ]

08:18.620 --> 08:20.040
H-Hey, everybody.

08:20.040 --> 08:21.080
This is Wyatt.

08:21.080 --> 08:23.210
Run, man. Run.

08:26.080 --> 08:27.500
Excuse me?

08:27.500 --> 08:29.790
Oh, no, sorry.
I'm watching another game.

08:29.790 --> 08:30.620
Fantasy football.

08:37.960 --> 08:41.080
I am so sorry. I didn't
realize how seriously
you guys took your football.

08:41.080 --> 08:43.380
It's okay. We were just
surprised to see those colors.

08:45.540 --> 08:47.290
Hey, Wyatt brought
some things in a bag.

08:47.290 --> 08:48.710
What you got in there,
Wyatt?

08:48.710 --> 08:50.620
Oh.

08:50.620 --> 08:53.000
Just some treats
I thought everyone might enjoy.

08:53.000 --> 08:55.500
This is a special trail mix
I make myself.

08:55.500 --> 08:57.120
I throw in dried mango.

08:57.120 --> 08:59.120
I know.
Crazy, right?

09:00.620 --> 09:03.790
Adds a zing,
and it's just instant energy.

09:03.790 --> 09:05.580
Congratulations, son.

09:05.580 --> 09:07.790
Two things that have never been
in this house --

09:07.790 --> 09:09.580
a Packers fan...

09:09.580 --> 09:11.210
and mango.

09:13.040 --> 09:14.460
What else
you got in there?

09:14.460 --> 09:16.710
Well, I also brought some beer.
O'Douls for Becky.

09:16.710 --> 09:19.210
Isn't that thoughtful?

09:19.210 --> 09:21.040
And regular beer
for everyone else.

09:21.040 --> 09:23.000
Cool.
Dad, you like beer.

09:23.000 --> 09:25.960
Wow. I do.
It's like we're the same person.

09:27.960 --> 09:29.790
I'm -- I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

09:29.790 --> 09:32.420
This is just Packer-phobia.

09:32.420 --> 09:34.210
We should give you
the benefit of the doubt.

09:34.210 --> 09:35.880
Thank you for the beer.

09:35.880 --> 09:37.040
Yeah.

09:37.040 --> 09:39.170
Uh, it's a small batch
organic IPA.

09:43.750 --> 09:45.790
I'll have an IPA. You know
what that stands for, don't you?

09:45.790 --> 09:47.290
Uh, India Pale Ale.

09:47.290 --> 09:49.580
I was gonna say "I Pee A-lot
when I drink beer."

09:52.380 --> 09:53.750
[ Laughs ]

09:53.750 --> 09:55.620
Here's a little factoid.

09:55.620 --> 09:58.620
I know Chicago loves its Bears,
but did you know the Packers

09:58.620 --> 10:01.290
are actually owned
by the people of Wisconsin?

10:01.290 --> 10:03.710
That's not football, son.
That's Communism.

10:04.920 --> 10:06.880
[ Cheering ]
Take the football!

10:06.880 --> 10:07.920
What a great hit!
Oh, yeah!

10:07.920 --> 10:09.250
He's done having kids!

10:09.250 --> 10:10.290
[ Laughter ]

10:10.290 --> 10:11.460
Oh.

10:11.460 --> 10:12.580
Wow.

10:12.580 --> 10:14.500
Maybe I'm mistaken,
but it sure seems like

10:14.500 --> 10:16.960
you guys are celebrating
because a player got hurt.

10:16.960 --> 10:18.830
It certainly
looks that way.

10:18.830 --> 10:20.500
Shame!

10:20.500 --> 10:24.080
Oh, Wyatt, if that was a Bear
limping off the field,

10:24.080 --> 10:25.210
you'd be celebrating.

10:25.210 --> 10:26.460
I wouldn't.

10:26.460 --> 10:29.500
Because, as a Christian,
I don't wish harm to anyone.

10:30.960 --> 10:33.580
The Crusades --
that was you guys, right?

10:33.580 --> 10:35.040
Oh!

10:35.040 --> 10:37.250
You want a little cream
for that burn, Wyatt?

10:38.830 --> 10:40.750
Mark, watch this replay.

10:40.750 --> 10:43.250
Now, see how we used play action
to freeze that linebacker?

10:43.250 --> 10:45.000
Does that always work?

10:45.000 --> 10:47.540
Sure, because Packers are
inherently dumber than Bears.

10:47.540 --> 10:49.210
Aunt Jackie!
[ Laughs ]

10:49.210 --> 10:51.000
That's okay.
I can take it.

10:51.000 --> 10:52.920
Oh, I'm surprised
you understood it.

10:52.920 --> 10:54.330
[ Laughs ]

10:54.330 --> 10:56.420
[ Cheering ]

10:56.420 --> 10:58.170
Yes! [ Laughs ]

10:58.170 --> 10:59.380
We win!

10:59.380 --> 11:01.330
Great game!

11:01.330 --> 11:04.040
It's only the first quarter,
but good energy! Yeah!

11:04.040 --> 11:05.920
Oh!
Eat it, Cheesehead!

11:05.920 --> 11:07.710
Hey!

11:07.710 --> 11:10.000
Wyatt is a guest.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.540
I understand the jealousy.

11:11.540 --> 11:13.080
The Bears
have won one Super Bowl,

11:13.080 --> 11:14.290
the Packers have won four.

11:14.290 --> 11:16.420
The trophy is called
the Lombardi Trophy,

11:16.420 --> 11:19.170
which, did I mention,
we've won four times?

11:20.380 --> 11:22.620
Ah, you got me there, Wyatt.
[ Groans ]

11:22.620 --> 11:24.540
Did I mention
that you're an udder-sucking,

11:24.540 --> 11:27.170
Rodgers-loving,
cow-tipping...

11:27.170 --> 11:29.170
dairy-dork loser?!

11:31.830 --> 11:33.120
Mary called it!

11:34.420 --> 11:35.420
[ Laughs ]

11:35.420 --> 11:37.710
♪♪

11:37.710 --> 11:40.500
Again, thanks for coming in
on a Sunday.

11:40.500 --> 11:42.830
I'm sure Ben'll find a parking
spot and be in here any minute.

11:42.830 --> 11:44.120
I know
we all want to get home

11:44.120 --> 11:45.880
and watch the Bears game
with our families.

11:45.880 --> 11:48.750
I always watch with my family.
It's a tradition.

11:48.750 --> 11:51.670
But...this is fun, too.

11:53.380 --> 11:55.080
[ Sighs ] Sorry.

11:56.620 --> 12:00.120
I put $2 in the meter,
and then I realized it's Sunday.

12:02.500 --> 12:05.330
Everything I touch
turns to crap.

12:06.830 --> 12:09.500
As you can see, we've expanded
on the Lock 'Em Up model.

12:09.500 --> 12:11.040
We have a new section

12:11.040 --> 12:13.830
that exposes local companies
who are doing sketchy stuff.

12:13.830 --> 12:15.540
That sounds interesting.

12:15.540 --> 12:19.330
I bought an accordion once
that came apart in my hands.

12:19.330 --> 12:20.380
[ Chuckles ]

12:20.380 --> 12:22.500
You give us a name,
we'll go get 'em.

12:23.790 --> 12:25.750
Uh, right.

12:25.750 --> 12:27.040
We're gonna get 'em.

12:29.170 --> 12:32.790
We're gonna go after
all the accordion guys.

12:32.790 --> 12:35.080
I do have one question.

12:35.080 --> 12:38.170
The magazine business as a whole
seems like it's on the decline.

12:38.170 --> 12:39.790
Are you ready
to buck that trend?

12:39.790 --> 12:42.210
Sure.

12:42.210 --> 12:44.750
Sounds pretty hard, though,
doesn't it?

12:46.170 --> 12:47.500
What -- What Ben
is trying to say

12:47.500 --> 12:50.170
is that we have a very
well-planned business strategy.

12:50.170 --> 12:51.170
She's right.

12:51.170 --> 12:53.960
We got a completely,
um...

12:53.960 --> 12:55.210
what do you call it?
Um...

12:56.580 --> 12:58.000
She's right.

13:00.080 --> 13:02.880
A lot of people
come in here over-rehearsed.

13:02.880 --> 13:04.290
Good for you guys.

13:07.000 --> 13:10.580
So, Ben, tell me more about
your departure from Lock 'Em Up.

13:10.580 --> 13:12.920
You know what -- I'm gonna
jump in and answer that,

13:12.920 --> 13:14.210
because otherwise,
he will.

13:14.210 --> 13:15.210
Um...

13:15.210 --> 13:18.040
I better...just go.

13:18.040 --> 13:19.290
I'm not helping here.

13:20.500 --> 13:21.330
I'll walk home.

13:24.460 --> 13:27.620
You know, I thought
everything would change
once I took the shower,

13:27.620 --> 13:30.120
but...it didn't.

13:32.420 --> 13:34.460
♪♪

13:34.460 --> 13:38.710
Chicken salad, potato salad,
macaroni salad.

13:38.710 --> 13:40.250
When your family
thinks of salad,

13:40.250 --> 13:42.960
it's not so much greens
as it is mayonnaise.

13:44.920 --> 13:46.040
How you holding up?

13:46.040 --> 13:47.460
I'm okay.

13:47.460 --> 13:49.750
Your family's
just having some fun with me.

13:49.750 --> 13:50.920
I don't see the reason

13:50.920 --> 13:53.000
why they had to drag my mother
into this.

13:54.290 --> 13:57.460
I'm sorry.
That was over the line.

13:57.460 --> 14:00.040
For the record, I don't think
she's a wild jackal

14:00.040 --> 14:02.250
that squatted out a Packers fan
in the woods.

14:04.040 --> 14:06.330
Oh,
for crying out loud!

14:06.330 --> 14:09.290
We got a quarterback
who trips over his own feet!

14:09.290 --> 14:11.920
How come our runner
always goes straight

14:11.920 --> 14:14.960
for the big pile of people
instead of the open part?

14:17.380 --> 14:18.960
'Cause then
we'd be a winning team,

14:18.960 --> 14:20.960
and that's not our way.

14:20.960 --> 14:23.040
Yes! Yes!

14:23.040 --> 14:24.960
Jackie, I told you

14:24.960 --> 14:26.960
I didn't want that
fantasy football stuff in here.

14:26.960 --> 14:30.000
I'm up $187.

14:30.000 --> 14:31.500
Here! It's five bucks.

14:31.500 --> 14:34.120
Go buy yourself
some "get off my ass."

14:37.880 --> 14:40.750
Oh!
He lost two yards!

14:40.750 --> 14:43.120
He's the worst person
in the history of the world!

14:44.670 --> 14:46.290
Hey, buddy,
it's just a game.

14:46.290 --> 14:48.120
Save that anger
for something important.

14:48.120 --> 14:50.080
The boy's just rooting
for his team.

14:50.080 --> 14:51.500
Sure.
And I love football, too,

14:51.500 --> 14:53.210
but at the end of the day,
it's just entertainment,

14:53.210 --> 14:55.330
like a game show
or magic or something.

14:55.330 --> 14:57.170
Ooooooooh...

14:58.710 --> 15:00.710
Magic?

15:00.710 --> 15:01.880
Did you say magic?

15:03.210 --> 15:05.540
You think a football game
is like some bozo

15:05.540 --> 15:08.210
pouring milk
into a top hat?

15:08.210 --> 15:10.040
Football's
kind of like magic.

15:10.040 --> 15:12.000
It's like
faking a hand-off.

15:12.000 --> 15:14.040
Who's got the ball?
Does that guy have the ball?

15:14.040 --> 15:15.210
No, it's that guy.

15:15.210 --> 15:17.500
20-yard play.
Whoa! It's magic.

15:19.210 --> 15:20.960
Come on, Mr. Conner,
you got to admit

15:20.960 --> 15:23.250
that some people
do take football too seriously.

15:23.250 --> 15:25.330
They sit on their couch
rather than hike or bike.

15:25.330 --> 15:27.830
If they put as much energy
into their real lives

15:27.830 --> 15:30.500
as they do into these games,
they'd accomplish a lot more.

15:33.120 --> 15:35.170
Are you talking about me,
Wyatt?

15:35.170 --> 15:36.790
I didn't mean
to offend you.

15:36.790 --> 15:38.540
Well, you did.

15:38.540 --> 15:41.040
Football is a big thing
in this family.

15:41.040 --> 15:43.290
Our team's struggles
are our struggles,

15:43.290 --> 15:45.710
and their successes
are our successes.

15:45.710 --> 15:49.620
Because sometimes we need a win
to get through the week.

15:49.620 --> 15:52.330
And who the hell are you
to pass judgment on that?

15:52.330 --> 15:54.080
Let's go, Wyatt.

15:55.620 --> 15:56.670
[ Door opens ]

15:56.670 --> 15:58.250
Wow. That was fast.

15:58.250 --> 16:00.170
I'm down
like a hundred bucks.

16:01.540 --> 16:03.500
I'm gonna need
that five back.

16:03.500 --> 16:04.500
♪♪

16:07.330 --> 16:09.880
Sorry about my family.

16:09.880 --> 16:12.080
I wish you met them
under better circumstances,

16:12.080 --> 16:14.330
like when they're asleep.

16:14.330 --> 16:15.380
Yeah.

16:15.380 --> 16:16.380
Boy.

16:16.380 --> 16:17.580
I gotta tell you,

16:17.580 --> 16:19.750
I give you a lot more credit
for staying sober.

16:19.750 --> 16:21.040
Thanks.

16:22.000 --> 16:23.080
Why is that?

16:23.080 --> 16:25.380
That's a challenging
environment.

16:25.380 --> 16:27.460
My family's
not the reason I drank.

16:27.460 --> 16:29.170
Couldn't have helped.

16:29.170 --> 16:31.000
There's a lot of anger
there.

16:31.000 --> 16:33.670
I mean, I get why y'all need
to escape into the game...

16:33.670 --> 16:35.040
and beer...

16:35.040 --> 16:36.380
and mayonnaise.

16:37.710 --> 16:39.710
That's not an escape.

16:39.710 --> 16:41.170
We love football.

16:41.170 --> 16:44.290
We love beer --
some of us too much.

16:44.290 --> 16:45.620
And you'd have to
pry the mayonnaise

16:45.620 --> 16:47.420
from our cold,
slippery hands.

16:49.420 --> 16:52.670
Look, I'm not trying
to upset you.

16:52.670 --> 16:54.830
I just think you and little Bev
deserve better.

16:54.830 --> 16:56.330
Better than what?

16:56.330 --> 16:58.580
All the support in the world
doesn't mean anything

16:58.580 --> 17:00.620
if you're constantly around
toxic people.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.380
Are you calling my family
toxic?

17:03.580 --> 17:05.620
What the hell
do you know about them?

17:05.620 --> 17:07.710
You were with them
for an hour.

17:07.710 --> 17:10.210
I'm glad I'm seeing
this side of you now.

17:10.210 --> 17:12.420
You are a judgmental,
holier-than-thou jerk!

17:13.620 --> 17:15.500
And you're boring!

17:15.500 --> 17:17.670
You're like trail mix
without the mango.

17:17.670 --> 17:19.040
No zing at all.

17:20.250 --> 17:21.710
This isn't even
a good fight!

17:21.710 --> 17:22.920
Get out!

17:22.920 --> 17:24.290
This is my car!

17:24.290 --> 17:25.710
I don't care!
Get out!

17:26.670 --> 17:28.210
F-Fine.

17:28.210 --> 17:30.000
But don't mess
with my pre-sets.

17:32.460 --> 17:33.670
[ Car door closes ]

17:33.670 --> 17:35.210
[ Beeping ]

17:39.120 --> 17:40.040
I am so sorry.

17:41.500 --> 17:43.670
I had a lot of time to think
on the way here,

17:43.670 --> 17:45.120
and I figured it out.

17:46.790 --> 17:49.460
I'm afraid to fail.

17:49.460 --> 17:51.790
You know,
the last time I did this...

17:51.790 --> 17:53.670
if I screwed up,
I only wrecked my life.

17:53.670 --> 17:56.920
Now, I'd take down you
and your kids with me.

17:56.920 --> 17:59.210
What? You think
failure's new to my kids?

17:59.210 --> 18:00.830
We eat failure
for breakfast.

18:00.830 --> 18:02.750
And we'd have it again
for lunch,

18:02.750 --> 18:05.710
but we failed to plan,
so we don't have any.

18:05.710 --> 18:07.250
So, you're gonna tell me

18:07.250 --> 18:10.250
you don't have any problems
taking this giant risk?

18:10.250 --> 18:12.790
You've already built
a successful mug shot magazine.

18:12.790 --> 18:14.420
Why can't you
just do it again?

18:14.420 --> 18:16.290
Because
it's not that easy.

18:16.290 --> 18:18.170
It was brutally hard
the first time,

18:18.170 --> 18:19.710
and it took
a hell of a lot of luck.

18:19.710 --> 18:21.290
Do you know
who was on the cover

18:21.290 --> 18:22.790
of the first issue
of Lock 'Em Up?

18:22.790 --> 18:24.420
The Lanford Cannibal.

18:24.420 --> 18:27.830
This guy ate his own foot
on a public bus.

18:27.830 --> 18:30.670
Now, what are the odds
of that happening again?

18:30.670 --> 18:32.580
I'm not gonna kid you, Ben.
They're not good.

18:34.210 --> 18:35.920
So, here is
what we're gonna do.

18:35.920 --> 18:39.170
I am gonna use you
for your credit rating,

18:39.170 --> 18:42.210
and you are
going to get out of my way.

18:42.210 --> 18:44.500
Well, that seems harsh.

18:46.000 --> 18:48.790
So, I taught you
everything I know,

18:48.790 --> 18:51.170
and you're just gonna use me
to get the money

18:51.170 --> 18:52.880
and then
make all the decisions?

18:52.880 --> 18:54.540
Yeah.
You're finally getting it.

18:54.540 --> 18:56.540
And what are you gonna do
about it? Take another shower?

18:56.540 --> 18:57.580
[ Chuckles ]

18:58.750 --> 19:01.420
N-No. I'm gonna --

19:01.420 --> 19:03.460
O...kay.

19:03.460 --> 19:05.670
I see what you're doing.
You're baiting me.

19:05.670 --> 19:09.080
No, I'm just pointing out
that you're a shell of a man.

19:09.080 --> 19:11.880
So I will build this thing,
and you'll greet me at the door,

19:11.880 --> 19:13.880
looking pretty
with a martini in your hand.

19:13.880 --> 19:15.670
What do you say
about that?

19:15.670 --> 19:17.620
Alright, yeah.
I'll play your little game.

19:17.620 --> 19:19.040
I'll let you
do all the work,

19:19.040 --> 19:21.380
and I'll stay in bed
and collect half the profits.

19:21.380 --> 19:24.170
Oh. Okay,
now you're baiting me.

19:24.170 --> 19:26.750
The baiter
has become the baitee.

19:26.750 --> 19:30.080
I think this conversation
has turned stupid.

19:34.500 --> 19:38.040
Now, for the record, I won't
be bringing you any martinis

19:38.040 --> 19:40.540
until you move up to a whole
better class of underwear.

19:40.540 --> 19:42.290
[ Chuckles ]

19:43.880 --> 19:46.040
[ Cheering on radio ]

19:46.040 --> 19:48.000
Well, I'm alone again.

19:48.000 --> 19:50.000
Aw, that's too bad.

19:50.000 --> 19:52.330
I was looking forward to backing
over Wyatt with my truck.

19:54.500 --> 19:56.420
I really wanted him
to be the one.

19:57.710 --> 19:59.540
[ Click ]
I don't get it.

19:59.540 --> 20:00.880
Why that guy?

20:00.880 --> 20:04.210
Because I thought he was steady
and dependable.

20:04.210 --> 20:06.380
Beverly Rose
needs somebody like that.

20:06.380 --> 20:09.000
Let the baby
get her own guy.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.120
You're not ready yet.

20:10.120 --> 20:11.880
What do you mean?

20:11.880 --> 20:15.080
I'm 44 years old, and I'm still
picking the wrong guys.

20:15.080 --> 20:17.120
My picker's broken.

20:17.120 --> 20:19.620
Look, you've been sober
for a minute.

20:19.620 --> 20:21.500
This is the first guy
you've dated.

20:23.170 --> 20:24.580
How are you supposed to know
what you want

20:24.580 --> 20:25.880
when you don't even know
who you are?

20:25.880 --> 20:27.500
I'm just gonna find

20:27.500 --> 20:30.080
the first decent,
weak-minded guy with a job

20:30.080 --> 20:31.920
and force him
to love me.

20:31.920 --> 20:35.830
Look, you just have to be
patient. It'll happen.

20:35.830 --> 20:38.540
And when it happens,
grab on tight to that person

20:38.540 --> 20:39.830
and never let them go.

20:39.830 --> 20:41.670
Thanks, Dad.

20:43.500 --> 20:46.330
Ugggh. I can't believe
I kissed a Cheesehead.

20:46.330 --> 20:48.210
Hey, hey, hey!
Keep that to yourself.

20:48.210 --> 20:49.710
I gotta live
in this neighborhood.

20:49.710 --> 20:51.120
♪♪

20:53.960 --> 20:56.330
What's going on?
The Bears came back!
We're within two.

20:56.330 --> 20:57.880
We got a chip-shot field goal
to win it.

20:57.880 --> 20:59.080
We prayed for this!

20:59.080 --> 21:00.920
I put a buck
in the collection basket.

21:02.290 --> 21:03.710
You muff this kick,
and I swear to God

21:03.710 --> 21:06.170
I will kill
everything you love.

21:06.170 --> 21:08.830
I don't know why I care so much
that he makes this.

21:08.830 --> 21:10.120
It's like
Stockholm Syndrome.

21:11.380 --> 21:14.380
I've taken on
the values of my captors.

21:14.380 --> 21:15.670
Announcer:
And it is good!

21:15.670 --> 21:18.290
[ Cheering ]

21:23.710 --> 21:25.330
I had the Bears' kicker!

21:25.330 --> 21:26.500
[ Cheering resumes ]
